	<h3>Who is Patrons for?</h3>
	<p>Anybody who has a supportive fan base: musicians, writers, comedians, filmmakers, podcasters, game developers, comic artists, bloggers, fine artists, open source developers, etc. In other words...you :)</p>

	<h3 style="margin-top:30px;">Is there a live demo that I can see?</h3>
	<p>Yep, check out our demo here: <a href="http://on.fb.me/patrons-demo">Patrons Demo</a></p>
	
	<h3 style="margin-top:30px;">What are the costs for Patrons?</h3>
	<p><strong>There are no upfront fees to use Patrons.</strong> The way Patrons works is that we charge a small administrative fee on your pledges, 5%. Our credit card payment processor also charges a fee for transactions, about 3%. Long story short: <strong>You get about 92% of the pledged money.</strong></p>
	
	
	<h3 style="margin-top:30px;">How do I get paid from Patrons?</h3>
	<p>We collect all of the payments from your fans throughout the month, then send you your money within 7 days of the end of the month. If you're account balance is less than $50, you're balance will be carried over to the next month. Currently all payouts are made via PayPal. We are looking at adding additional payout options in the future.</p>

